    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Empirical Results\"\nsubtitle: \"Main Regression Results and Coefficient Visualizations\"\ndate: last-modified\n---\n\n\n\nThis page presents the main regression results. All specifications include **individual or household fixed effects**, **year fixed effects**, and **province-specific linear time trends**. Standard errors are clustered at the village (sous-colline) level. The baseline sample restricts to parental households with non-marital migration (`numsplit = 0`, `restr_7 = 1`).\n\nThe estimating equations are:\n\n**Individual-level (Eq. 1):**\n$$\\text{Leave}_{iht} = \\alpha_i + \\delta_t + \\gamma_{p(h)} \\cdot t + \\beta \\cdot \\text{Conflict}_{v(h)t} + \\varepsilon_{iht}$$\n\n**Household-level (Eq. 2):**\n$$Y_{ht} = \\mu_h + \\delta_t + \\gamma_{p(h)} \\cdot t + \\beta \\cdot X_{ht} + \\varepsilon_{ht}$$\n\n---\n\n## Non-Marital Migration (Individual Level)\n\n**Table 3** estimates Equation 1 for individual non-marital migration. Each column uses a different measure of conflict: village-level binary exposure (cols. 1), continuous intensity (col. 2), individual victimization types (cols. 3–7), and composite PCA indices (cols. 8–10).\n\n\n::: {#tbl-individual .cell tbl-cap='Table 3 <U+2014> Effect of Conflict on Individual Non-Marital Migration'}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table class=\"table\" style=\"font-size: 12px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;border-bottom: 0;\">\n <thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"empty-cells: hide;border-bottom:hidden;\" colspan=\"1\"></th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom:hidden;padding-bottom:0; padding-left:3px;padding-right:3px;text-align: center; \" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 5px; \">Village level</div></th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom:hidden;padding-bottom:0; padding-left:3px;padding-right:3px;text-align: center; \" colspan=\"4\"><div style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 5px; \">Household victimization</div></th>\n<th st