lign:left;\"> Province &lt;U+00D7&gt; Year trend </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> Yes </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> Yes </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> Yes </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> Yes </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> Yes </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> Yes </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> Yes </td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n<tfoot><tr><td style=\"padding: 0; \" colspan=\"100%\">\n<span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Notes:</span> <sup></sup> Dependent variable: indicator = 1 if individual migrated for non-marital reasons in year t. All specifications include individual FE, year FE, and province-specific time trends. Standard errors clustered at the village (sous-colline) level in brackets. *** p&lt;0.01, ** p&lt;0.05, * p&lt;0.10.</td></tr></tfoot>\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n\n::: {.callout-note}\n**Interpretation — Column (1):** A village-year with any conflict casualties increases the probability of non-marital migration by **3.1 percentage points** (off a dep. var. mean of 4.5%). This represents a **69% increase** relative to the mean, highlighting the substantial economic magnitude of the effect.\n:::\n\n### Visualizing the Mechanism\n\nThe pattern across columns reveals that the effect of village-level violence (cols. 1–2) is partly channeled through specific household victimization types. Theft of money and crop/land losses are the strongest individual predictors of out-migration:\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![Estimated Effects on Non-Marital Migration — Point Estimates with 95% CIs](results_files/figure-html/fig-coefficients-t3-1.png){#fig-coefficients-t3 width=1400}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Non-Marital Migration (Household Level)\n\n**Table 4** estimates Equation 2 at the household level. The outcome is whether *any* household member migrated for non-marital reasons in year $t$.\n\n\n::: {#tbl-household .cell tbl-cap='Table 4 <U+2014> Effect of Conflict on Household Migration'}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table class=\"table\" style=\"font-size: 10.5px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;border-bottom: 0;\">\n <thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"empty-cells: hide;border-bottom:hidden;\" colspan=\"1\"></th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom:hidden;padding-bottom:0; padding-left:3px;padding-right:3px;text-align: center; \" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 5px; \">Village level</div></th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom:hidden;padding-bottom:0; padding-left:3px;padding-right:3px;text-align: center; \" colspan=\"5\"><div style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 5px; \">HH victimization</div></th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom:hidden;padding-bottom:0; padding-left:3px;padding-right:3px;text-align: center; \" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 5px; \">PCA</div></th>\n</tr>\n  <tr>\n   <th style=\"text-align:left;\"> Variable </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (1) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (2) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (3) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (4) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (5) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (6) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (7) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (8) </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> (9) </th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> Violence (exposure) </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\"> 0.041*** </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:center;\">  </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\">  </td>\n   <td style=\"t